rComments: Lovely professor who actually cares about her students. Friendliest professor ever. Also, very Canadian, love it.
Good lectures, easy weekly tests based on only the plot, easy to read rubrics, and a great atmosphere.

Amazing professor. She gives 3 possible midterm questions ahead of time and picks one. Lots of options for the essay. Funny, and always trying to meet her students half-way. She even organized a pizza night for our 5:30-8:30 class. Definitely would take a class with her again.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Great prof.  -Interesting lectures. Extremely friendly prof. -Attendance is essentially mandatory. Slides are incomplete and left for students to fill out. Also strongly encourages attendance through participation grade.  -2500 to 3000 word paper. Was not marked difficultly. Gives clear expectation for midterm and exams.

She made the Friday 5:30-8:30 class enjoyable and something I looked forward to. She's funny and engaging with students and sincerely wants her students to do well in her class. She's also so beautiful, which doesn't hurt.
Amazing professor. She makes complex material easy to understand and brings a lot of energy to her lectures. Highly recommended. Also, she is incredibly easy on the eyes.
